            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>[name] ... the infant, who died on the fifth day before the Ides(?) of September, having lived...</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The restorations are to some extent exempli gratia, since e.g. the Kalends is possible instead of the Ides, and October and November are also possible restorations for the month. It is not clear where the second fragment fits in (the letters are smaller, but the marble is the same). Although Tréziny suggest lambda is also possible, from the photograph alpha looks reasonably certain. As Tréziny notes, there appears to be a vacat after the second letter.</p>
            </div>
